Enterprise learning and hiring processes are largely disconnected and ineffective in evaluating real-world skills. Training programs are passive and lack engagement, leading to poor knowledge retention, while candidate screening methods rely on resumes and theoretical assessments that fail to measure practical decision-making. This creates a gap where employees and candidates are not adequately prepared or evaluated for real-world scenarios, especially in critical domains like fraud detection, risk management, and operations. There is a need for a unified, interactive approach that both enhances learning and accurately assesses real-world problem-solving abilities.
